WEBVTT

1
00:01:02.833 --> 00:01:03.833
Let's go!

2
00:01:12.750 --> 00:01:14.250
All right. let's go!

3
00:01:35.583 --> 00:01:38.833
When everyone stands up.
drop your backpack.

4
00:01:53.167 --> 00:01:54.167
Where's Jane?

5
00:01:54.667 --> 00:01:55.833
Daniel Kernner

6
00:01:56.333 --> 00:01:58.167
Do you want to see her again?

7
00:02:09.917 --> 00:02:11.083
Calm down.

8
00:02:11.417 --> 00:02:12.667
Enjoy the show!

9
00:02:12.833 --> 00:02:14.833
She must be checking the contents.

10
00:02:19.750 --> 00:02:23.417
From July 23. 1948… 83

11
00:02:23.583 --> 00:02:28.383
Until March 14. 1984

12
00:02:29.617 --> 00:02:34.333
There are
a total of 107 128GB IronClad cards.

13
00:02:34.500 --> 00:02:37.583
- Should we count them again?
- Not until we're all done.

14
00:02:37.750 --> 00:02:40.333
Paper documents: approximately 200 pages

15
00:02:40.500 --> 00:02:41.833
What era is it from?

16
00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:43.667
I'll make the catalog later.

17
00:02:43.833 --> 00:02:48.250
The oldest one dates back to 1947.
The most recent one appears to be from last year.

18
00:03:28.500 --> 00:03:30.500
This is very unfortunate.

19
00:03:33.500 --> 00:03:34.667
Where's Jane?

20
00:03:45.417 --> 00:03:46.367
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

21
00:03:48.417 --> 00:03:49.500
Watch out!

22
00:04:01.583 --> 00:04:03.000
Who did he switch sides to?

23
00:04:03.583 --> 00:04:07.167
Tell me everyone's names.
Then I'll call you a taxi.

24
00:04:07.417 --> 00:04:08.500
It's right here

25
00:04:33.417 --> 00:04:34.333
Where is it?

26
00:04:40.083 --> 00:04:41.417
Put down your weapons!

27
00:04:41.583 --> 00:04:44.083
Don't shoot!

28
00:04:45.000 --> 00:04:47.583
If I shoot it.
it might start up.

29
00:04:49.583 --> 00:04:51.167
Loosen Your Fist. Daniel

30
00:04:52.250 --> 00:04:54.333
It works when you tighten it.
Let go.

31
00:04:56.250 --> 00:04:57.583
You probably don't know how to use it.

32
00:04:57.833 --> 00:04:58.917
I had watched how it was done

33
00:04:59.083 --> 00:05:00.667
And I nearly died

34
00:05:00.833 --> 00:05:03.083
Put that on the ground.

35
00:05:03.583 --> 00:05:05.167
You all deserve what's coming to you.

36
00:05:05.333 --> 00:05:06.833
Put the gun down. Serena

37
00:05:10.833 --> 00:05:13.417
Don't tense your fingers.

38
00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:15.250
Loosen your fist.

39
00:05:16.500 --> 00:05:18.000
Loosen it...  Right.

40
00:05:18.167 --> 00:05:19.167
Open your hand

41
00:05:20.667 --> 00:05:21.583
Right.

42
00:05:25.167 --> 00:05:27.917
Put everything back in the bag
and get in the car.

43
00:05:31.417 --> 00:05:32.417
Get lost

44
00:05:39.083 --> 00:05:43.583
I'm not
hiding behind the screen
and messing around with malware. you know.

45
00:05:43.833 --> 00:05:45.000
The world is undergoing drastic changes

46
00:05:45.250 --> 00:05:49.917
If we disclose everything.
it will only lead to dangerous chaos.

47
00:05:51.583 --> 00:05:52.833
I looked at the interrogation transcript.

48
00:05:54.083 --> 00:05:57.333
History cannot be reset.
It becomes irreversible.

49
00:05:59.917 --> 00:06:01.167
That's the plan.

50
00:06:15.667 --> 00:06:16.667
Void!

51
00:06:21.667 --> 00:06:23.417
To the guy who's supposed to be sitting at his desk

52
00:06:24.667 --> 00:06:26.250
How did they get the better of me?

53
00:06:35.417 --> 00:06:36.667
Are you a traitor?

54
00:06:36.917 --> 00:06:39.667
They aren't government agencies.
Their job is to lie.

55
00:06:39.833 --> 00:06:41.500
Tell me what's going on.

56
00:06:42.250 --> 00:06:44.250
The car is being tracked.
We have to disable it.

57
00:06:44.500 --> 00:06:46.667
- Aren't you going to walk me home?
- They're lying in wait.

58
00:06:47.667 --> 00:06:49.500
Hand me that case

59
00:06:54.167 --> 00:06:55.083
The steering wheel

60
00:07:05.917 --> 00:07:07.417
Hugo:  Got it.

61
00:07:07.667 --> 00:07:10.167
Daniel! Good job!

62
00:07:10.417 --> 00:07:12.333
They kidnapped Jane.

63
00:07:12.500 --> 00:07:13.833
I found it!

64
00:07:14.167 --> 00:07:15.333
Is she okay?

65
00:07:15.833 --> 00:07:17.333
I wouldn't say so.  Hugo

66
00:07:17.917 --> 00:07:18.917
Where should I send it?

67
00:07:19.083 --> 00:07:21.917
Don't deliver it now—hide yourself…

68
00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:26.583
Send someone over right away.
I need someone to help me carry this.

69
00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:27.833
That's your job.

70
00:07:28.500 --> 00:07:29.500
It's your turn.

71
00:07:30.833 --> 00:07:32.333
I don't want to do it!

72
00:07:32.500 --> 00:07:35.417
I took it out of the facility… and I did it.

73
00:07:35.583 --> 00:07:38.417
When it comes to preserving the documents.
you're the best person for the job.

74
00:07:38.583 --> 00:07:39.750
Are you out of your mind?

75
00:07:41.917 --> 00:07:45.333
I'm not an agent.
I'm an engineer.

76
00:07:45.583 --> 00:07:47.750
Trust me.  Everything's going according to plan.

77
00:07:47.917 --> 00:07:50.167
Waiting for someone to start it up

78
00:07:50.667 --> 00:07:52.750
When the time comes.
we should be able to work together.

79
00:07:52.917 --> 00:07:55.417
Take Jane to a safe place
and hide out tonight.

80
00:07:56.333 --> 00:07:58.000
I can't do it alone

81
00:07:58.083 --> 00:07:59.667
It's better for her if you're not around.

82
00:07:59.833 --> 00:08:00.833
You must have realized that wasn't the case!

83
00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:03.583
Once you get to the hideout.
tell me where you are.

84
00:08:03.750 --> 00:08:05.833
Santiago will be joining us in the morning.

85
00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:09.000
Everything should be made available online
immediately

86
00:08:10.833 --> 00:08:13.917
Whatever you do. don't do that.

87
00:08:15.750 --> 00:08:16.833
I'm on standby right now.

88
00:08:17.167 --> 00:08:20.667
Be careful.  Find a shelter.
Santiago will get in touch.

89
00:08:21.750 --> 00:08:23.000
Destroy the device

90
00:08:26.500 --> 00:08:27.500
Danny!

91
00:08:27.667 --> 00:08:29.500
It's a disposable device.

92
00:08:29.833 --> 00:08:32.667
Using a proprietary encrypted network.
it's a one-time. single-use code.

93
00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:38.167
What kind of job do you actually have?

94
00:08:39.833 --> 00:08:40.917
I have to find a shelter.

95
00:08:41.083 --> 00:08:43.000
It's neither an apartment nor a motel

96
00:08:43.167 --> 00:08:45.583
It's a place
I've never been to before.

97
00:08:47.333 --> 00:08:49.167
I know a place nearby.

98
00:08:54.333 --> 00:08:58.083
Wardex Headquarters
Occoquan. Virginia

99
00:09:03.250 --> 00:09:05.917
Mazgrave of the Department of Defense is requesting a report

100
00:09:06.083 --> 00:09:08.333
Call Wakefield right away.

101
00:09:08.500 --> 00:09:11.417
Tell Mazgrave
that it was just a minor problem.

102
00:09:11.667 --> 00:09:13.583
You should be the one to report it.

103
00:09:13.833 --> 00:09:16.083
This would reveal their concerns

104
00:09:16.250 --> 00:09:20.083
The military and intelligence agencies are going to swarm in within an hour.

105
00:09:20.167 --> 00:09:21.250
Take care of it.

106
00:09:21.417 --> 00:09:23.083
Is this in the news?

107
00:09:23.250 --> 00:09:24.417
Not yet.

108
00:09:24.583 --> 00:09:27.250
- What about social media and the internet?
- Nothing out of the ordinary

109
00:09:31.083 --> 00:09:32.583
Twelve people are absent today.

110
00:09:36.333 --> 00:09:37.750
All the desks are empty.

111
00:09:38.167 --> 00:09:40.000
All of them hold a security clearance of G5 or higher.

112
00:09:49.167 --> 00:09:51.500
In other words. this is

113
00:09:51.667 --> 00:09:54.667
It was a carefully planned and executed operation.

114
00:09:55.833 --> 00:09:58.083
Why? What's the point?

115
00:09:58.583 --> 00:10:02.333
If they intended to spread the archive.
they would have done so long ago.

116
00:10:02.500 --> 00:10:04.667
Someone is delaying the decision.

117
00:10:04.833 --> 00:10:07.750
But how long will this last? Think fast.

118
00:10:08.417 --> 00:10:10.350
Daniel Kernner
Holds a Ph.D. in cybersecurity

119
00:10:11.833 --> 00:10:15.083
We have been protecting confidential data for eight years.

120
00:10:15.250 --> 00:10:18.000
What do you know about him? What are your thoughts?

121
00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:20.417
Can bypass the firewall

122
00:10:20.583 --> 00:10:22.083
Enough of that. Let's think about our next move.

123
00:10:22.250 --> 00:10:24.917
- Keep skip tracking enabled
- Have access to SYNTRAK

124
00:10:25.083 --> 00:10:26.667
I use disposable ones

125
00:10:27.250 --> 00:10:28.333
President

126
00:10:29.333 --> 00:10:31.750
Hugo hasn't come to work.

127
00:10:34.250 --> 00:10:35.750
My desk is empty. too.

128
00:10:36.750 --> 00:10:37.750
Hugo

129
00:10:41.167 --> 00:10:43.583
The second control unit disappeared

130
00:10:44.333 --> 00:10:45.583
Where's number three?

131
00:10:46.083 --> 00:10:47.750
The cooler is locked.

132
00:11:27.500 --> 00:11:29.167
Will you really open it for me?

133
00:11:30.333 --> 00:11:31.833
That's just how it's agreed upon

134
00:11:33.250 --> 00:11:34.583
How do you know about this place?

135
00:11:49.217 --> 00:11:51.800
The bishop finally wore sneakers.

136
00:11:53.417 --> 00:11:55.417
I hated those shoes.

137
00:11:55.583 --> 00:11:57.833
There was a terrible screeching sound. and

138
00:12:02.083 --> 00:12:05.083
I felt so lonely. I love you so much.

139
00:12:05.333 --> 00:12:08.583
I've been nothing but a burden to everyone all this time

140
00:12:09.067 --> 00:12:12.233
You're still speaking your mind. aren't you?

141
00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:15.667
- Has Teresa finished her training?
- She did a great job.

142
00:12:15.917 --> 00:12:17.833
After I stop sneaking out at night...

143
00:12:18.917 --> 00:12:22.750
The bishop entrusted
primary education at St. Anthony's to me.

144
00:12:22.917 --> 00:12:24.667
You should know how to handle kids. right?

145
00:12:29.917 --> 00:12:32.167
Hold this up to your eye

146
00:12:39.917 --> 00:12:43.417
I won't ask any questions. I'm not interested.

147
00:12:44.333 --> 00:12:45.333
But Jane is different.

148
00:12:46.667 --> 00:12:49.750
No matter what you did. you should take responsibility.

149
00:12:50.417 --> 00:12:52.750
So. don't drag Jane into this.

150
00:12:53.583 --> 00:12:55.667
Just leave it here.

151
00:13:00.583 --> 00:13:01.833
Was she a nun?

152
00:13:03.417 --> 00:13:05.833
We've slept together—what are you suspicious about?

153
00:13:06.750 --> 00:13:09.750
The fact that he didn't tell me everything

154
00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:13.083
That's what they always say!

155
00:13:14.500 --> 00:13:18.167
I couldn't talk about it because I had to keep it a secret.
But you...

156
00:13:19.250 --> 00:13:21.000
So she was a nun!

157
00:13:21.667 --> 00:13:22.917
Apprentice.

158
00:13:23.167 --> 00:13:24.167
Why did you hide it?

159
00:13:24.333 --> 00:13:26.917
Because I didn't want to be criticized

160
00:13:30.333 --> 00:13:31.917
Since when?

161
00:13:33.333 --> 00:13:34.500
It was three years ago.

162
00:13:35.417 --> 00:13:37.750
I'll answer. but it's your turn first.

163
00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:41.167
What did you steal?

164
00:13:43.833 --> 00:13:46.583
That's the data they were supposed to protect.

165
00:13:46.833 --> 00:13:48.333
Why would you do that?

166
00:13:49.833 --> 00:13:51.500
People have the right to know the truth.

167
00:13:52.817 --> 00:13:53.650
You stole it. didn't you?

168
00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:56.167
What kind of truth is that. exactly?

169
00:14:00.250 --> 00:14:04.083
I wanted to become a nun.
but you…

170
00:14:05.167 --> 00:14:06.667
I've lost my calling.

171
00:14:07.500 --> 00:14:09.583
How long have you been working for them?

172
00:14:10.083 --> 00:14:11.333
Eight years ago…

173
00:14:15.750 --> 00:14:17.333
After being released from prison.

174
00:14:18.250 --> 00:14:20.500
Right away.

175
00:14:24.250 --> 00:14:25.250
I served 19 months in prison.

176
00:14:26.000 --> 00:14:28.500
In St. Petersburg. for cybercrime. you see...

177
00:14:29.333 --> 00:14:32.417
On the day I was released from prison.
Wardex scouted me in the parking lot.

178
00:14:33.333 --> 00:14:35.833
- Even though he has a criminal record?
- That's exactly why he has a criminal record.

179
00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:41.417
It was my job to keep secrets.
I'm not against you guys.

180
00:14:41.917 --> 00:14:45.500
Three months ago. I knew
much less than I do now.

181
00:14:50.333 --> 00:14:52.083
I'm doing the right thing.

182
00:14:53.750 --> 00:14:57.583
The data I stole—
they have no right to it.

183
00:14:57.833 --> 00:15:00.000
Everyone should know the truth.

184
00:15:00.250 --> 00:15:02.833
Just like air and light. it doesn't belong to Wardex.

185
00:15:03.083 --> 00:15:05.083
Belongs to no one

186
00:15:06.667 --> 00:15:08.000
What I stole was

187
00:15:08.583 --> 00:15:10.917
It belongs to 8 billion people

188
00:15:11.917 --> 00:15:13.583
It belongs to the whole world.

189
00:15:15.750 --> 00:15:17.583
And now there’s no turning back for me

190
00:15:20.250 --> 00:15:21.667
The only downside is

191
00:15:23.250 --> 00:15:25.417
I've dragged you into this

192
00:15:30.667 --> 00:15:33.583
Warm. humid air
is stagnating in this area

193
00:15:33.833 --> 00:15:37.167
It collided with a cold front coming from the north

194
00:15:37.417 --> 00:15:39.950
The warm air will be pushed up into the troposphere.

195
00:15:40.367 --> 00:15:42.533
Causes large-scale condensation

196
00:15:43.000 --> 00:15:44.917
If it rises sharply.

197
00:15:45.083 --> 00:15:48.583
The sudden cooling will trigger
my favorite kind of precipitation.

198
00:15:48.750 --> 00:15:49.833
It can't be helped. can it?

199
00:15:50.083 --> 00:15:52.250
I'm sorry... I just can't stop.

200
00:15:52.417 --> 00:15:53.450
Hail! Hail!

201
00:15:53.667 --> 00:15:55.250
Weather Cha-Cha-Cha!

202
00:16:14.083 --> 00:16:16.583
Don't bother Chacha—I love her so much!

203
00:16:16.750 --> 00:16:20.000
- It might become a trend.
- You could make a fortune.

204
00:16:20.500 --> 00:16:23.167
- I told you not to look.
- But it's the best!

205
00:16:23.333 --> 00:16:24.417
Stop it.

206
00:16:24.583 --> 00:16:26.500
Chacha is sexy.

207
00:16:26.833 --> 00:16:28.833
- Are you going to keep going?
- Do you like it?

208
00:16:29.500 --> 00:16:32.333
Yeah. really.
I can't be the only one.

209
00:16:32.750 --> 00:16:34.417
I know this might sound a bit presumptuous. but...

210
00:16:34.583 --> 00:16:38.000
Didn't the forecast turn out to be wrong?

211
00:16:38.417 --> 00:16:39.833
To be honest……

212
00:16:41.333 --> 00:16:42.417
I can't believe it's hailing!

213
00:16:43.083 --> 00:16:44.833
Did you see what I sent?

214
00:16:46.750 --> 00:16:47.500
What are you talking about?

215
00:16:47.667 --> 00:16:48.750
It's an audition!

216
00:16:51.583 --> 00:16:54.000
Sorry. I forgot.

217
00:16:54.167 --> 00:16:55.917
Watch Now

218
00:16:56.083 --> 00:16:57.833
Gunter recorded it.

219
00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:00.583
The KCXE anchors
write their own scripts. so

220
00:17:00.750 --> 00:17:02.250
I'm the one who wrote it.

221
00:17:02.500 --> 00:17:03.750
Remember that. okay?

222
00:17:06.417 --> 00:17:08.500
This is Margaret Fairchild from KCXE.

223
00:17:08.667 --> 00:17:09.667
Here's the news from Kansas City

224
00:17:09.917 --> 00:17:12.500
Concerns Over News from Pyongyang

225
00:17:12.667 --> 00:17:14.083
ARG dissidents

226
00:17:14.250 --> 00:17:18.417
Four new
military bases have been built on the east side of the Nakdong River

227
00:17:18.583 --> 00:17:21.500
Nuclear weapons are deployed at two of them

228
00:17:21.667 --> 00:17:26.083
At the same time. Russian television stations have been
repeatedly issuing threats against Seoul. and

229
00:17:26.500 --> 00:17:29.333
It mentions
the troops that had gathered at the 38th Parallel

230
00:17:29.500 --> 00:17:30.500
Up north.

231
00:17:30.667 --> 00:17:33.750
Vice Marshal Park Myung-soo
is asserting his authority.

232
00:17:35.583 --> 00:17:36.667
Good

233
00:17:36.833 --> 00:17:39.167
Very good. Perfect.

234
00:17:39.333 --> 00:17:42.333
Really?
Oh. that's great—it's perfect.

235
00:17:43.750 --> 00:17:45.250
As always. this is amazing!

236
00:17:45.417 --> 00:17:47.500
And I really
love the job you're doing now.

237
00:17:49.750 --> 00:17:51.500
She's a successful weathercaster

238
00:17:53.083 --> 00:17:55.750
She's KCXE's poster girl.

239
00:17:56.250 --> 00:17:58.417
Should I call it “K-Sexy”?

240
00:17:59.333 --> 00:18:00.833
You should move.

241
00:18:04.833 --> 00:18:06.017
- Again?
- Yeah

242
00:18:06.250 --> 00:18:09.833
I just put up new wallpaper.
and you want to go somewhere again?

243
00:18:10.000 --> 00:18:12.083
- What are you aiming for?
- I don't know...

244
00:18:12.250 --> 00:18:14.000
Be more ambitious.  Think bigger.

245
00:18:14.167 --> 00:18:16.333
Weren't you in Dallas?
Weren't you ambitious?

246
00:18:16.583 --> 00:18:19.000
Dallas just wasn't the right fit for me.

247
00:18:19.750 --> 00:18:21.583
It wasn't the place for me.

248
00:18:23.333 --> 00:18:26.250
So. where do you belong. Maggie?

249
00:18:29.167 --> 00:18:31.000
You'll see when you get there.

250
00:18:31.417 --> 00:18:32.500
I guess so.

251
00:18:35.000 --> 00:18:37.250
Can't you just relax for a little while?

252
00:18:39.833 --> 00:18:41.833
- It's nice to be here.
- I know.

253
00:18:42.250 --> 00:18:43.333
I'm really on a roll right now.

254
00:18:43.500 --> 00:18:46.000
I'm playing my own songs.
so I'm not going to DJ anymore.

255
00:18:46.167 --> 00:18:49.417
On Wednesdays and Saturdays. I play
at McPhillies

256
00:18:50.417 --> 00:18:54.333
Just because you pack your bags
doesn't mean all your problems will be solved.

257
00:18:58.167 --> 00:18:59.083
Look

258
00:19:20.167 --> 00:19:21.417
Get lost!

259
00:19:22.917 --> 00:19:23.833
Get out!

260
00:19:27.250 --> 00:19:28.667
What a cheeky bird!

261
00:19:34.667 --> 00:19:36.083
Mag. are you okay?

262
00:19:38.667 --> 00:19:40.417
He looks like he's not feeling well.

263
00:19:41.841 --> 00:19:44.041
