What am I doing?

784
01:02:01.667 --> 01:02:02.667
Get out.

785
01:02:02.917 --> 01:02:03.917
Get out of the car.

786
01:02:45.067 --> 01:02:46.233
Buckle up!

787
01:03:31.417 --> 01:03:32.750
He's having a seizure.
Watch your head.

788
01:03:33.167 --> 01:03:34.500
- Let me sleep
- I'm going to bite my tongue

789
01:03:48.567 --> 01:03:49.817
Get down!

790
01:04:09.000 --> 01:04:10.917
Jane: It's not you.

791
01:04:11.083 --> 01:04:12.333
Hey. Scanlon!

792
01:04:12.500 --> 01:04:13.750
Give me the command!

793
01:04:13.917 --> 01:04:15.583
I'm going to flip it over at 3.

794
01:04:22.250 --> 01:04:23.583
What happened?

795
01:04:29.583 --> 01:04:30.500
Go get it!

796
01:04:30.667 --> 01:04:31.833
I have some gloves I'm going to take.

797
01:04:49.333 --> 01:04:51.083
Look behind you.
What do you see?

798
01:04:57.500 --> 01:04:59.833
Dust. oh dust
Just dust

799
01:05:01.583 --> 01:05:02.583
They're coming!

800
01:05:29.067 --> 01:05:29.900
Hurry!

801
01:05:31.333 --> 01:05:32.333
Wait

802
01:05:34.500 --> 01:05:36.667
What are you doing?
- Put it in drive!

803
01:06:03.917 --> 01:06:05.200
It fell!

804
01:06:05.667 --> 01:06:07.083
In the water

805
01:06:08.500 --> 01:06:09.667
Call a diver

806
01:06:33.083 --> 01:06:34.833
They think the world
has come to an end.

807
01:06:35.083 --> 01:06:36.333
I can't afford to dawdle.

808
01:06:36.583 --> 01:06:39.833
Kerner will be here soon.
We have to head north.

809
01:06:40.500 --> 01:06:42.583
I have to get back to the hospital.

810
01:06:43.250 --> 01:06:45.083
This isn't something that can be treated.

811
01:06:45.250 --> 01:06:46.833
Do you
know what your problem is?

812
01:06:47.000 --> 01:06:48.667
Do you think there's something wrong with me?

813
01:06:48.833 --> 01:06:49.750
Look at me

814
01:06:52.750 --> 01:06:54.083
If I go.  you'll stay behind

815
01:06:56.067 --> 01:06:58.817
I want you to go.
but you're staying here.

816
01:07:21.583 --> 01:07:24.250
Hey. about what's been happening to me...

817
01:07:26.417 --> 01:07:29.833
It's not like I'm the one making it happen.
It's as if I've become a passenger.

818
01:07:30.750 --> 01:07:34.333
It's not a bad thing.
If anything. it's actually really positive.

819
01:07:35.583 --> 01:07:37.167
Just like your music

820
01:07:37.667 --> 01:07:39.417
You know. when you're in the zone

821
01:07:40.000 --> 01:07:41.250
And myself…

822
01:07:43.750 --> 01:07:45.083
I'm in the zone.

823
01:07:46.917 --> 01:07:50.083
Once you figure out where you belong.
you promised you'd tell me. right?

824
01:07:51.583 --> 01:07:52.667
That's exactly how it is right now.

825
01:07:53.667 --> 01:07:56.333
Right now. I'm where I belong.

826
01:08:00.583 --> 01:08:02.000
We should head north

827
01:08:02.500 --> 01:08:05.250
Is it because Kern is there?

828
01:08:05.417 --> 01:08:07.833
I'm sorry.  That's not right.
He's in the east.

829
01:08:08.250 --> 01:08:10.333
- It's east right now. isn't it?
- How do you know?

830
01:08:10.500 --> 01:08:12.750
It's just a hunch.

831
01:08:13.917 --> 01:08:15.917
But he's somewhere in the East.

832
01:08:16.667 --> 01:08:17.750
Where?

833
01:08:20.167 --> 01:08:21.667
Should I take over the wheel?

834
01:08:23.750 --> 01:08:25.083
Go buy some water

835
01:08:42.083 --> 01:08:43.083
Hey

836
01:08:48.317 --> 01:08:49.483
I have a favor to ask...

837
01:08:49.833 --> 01:08:50.750
Dr. Coleman?

838
01:08:51.833 --> 01:08:53.667
Thank you for answering the phone.

839
01:08:54.583 --> 01:08:56.500
I don't know. She ran away...

840
01:08:57.250 --> 01:08:58.833
It's getting worse and worse

841
01:08:59.750 --> 01:09:02.333
Yeah. thanks.
Please don't cut it.

842
01:09:02.500 --> 01:09:05.000
Excuse me.
Do you know the address of this place?

843
01:09:05.067 --> 01:09:07.317
Decatur. 37 Pearl Street

844
01:09:07.741 --> 01:09:09.741
Decatur. 37 Pearl Street

845
01:09:11.500 --> 01:09:13.083
We look forward to seeing you.  Thank you.

846
01:09:13.333 --> 01:09:14.583
Tiger
Mart

847
01:09:24.250 --> 01:09:25.333
Sorry!

848
01:09:26.833 --> 01:09:30.500
I love you. but
I was told to tell you that I'm heading east.

849
01:09:47.067 --> 01:09:48.400
Why Kansas City?

850
01:09:49.583 --> 01:09:51.833
The important thing is to be there tomorrow.

851
01:09:52.000 --> 01:09:53.833
Hugo: I...

852
01:09:56.500 --> 01:09:59.500
My memory is starting to come back

853
01:10:00.083 --> 01:10:01.250
What kind of memory is that?

854
01:10:01.667 --> 01:10:02.833
Animals

855
01:10:03.333 --> 01:10:06.417
A compassionate yet terrifying animal
is staring at me

856
01:10:08.333 --> 01:10:11.083
Can't you take your eyes off it?

857
01:10:11.750 --> 01:10:14.083
Yeah. we have to put them first.

858
01:10:17.083 --> 01:10:19.500
Is it a memory? Or a dream?

859
01:10:20.750 --> 01:10:22.000
I don't know

860
01:10:26.583 --> 01:10:27.500
Daniel

861
01:10:33.500 --> 01:10:36.417
It wasn't you
who got them to hire me. was it?

862
01:10:36.583 --> 01:10:39.500
It's not just this mission—
it's also about getting hired at Wardex.

863
01:10:42.250 --> 01:10:43.583
Oh. that's right.

864
01:10:44.167 --> 01:10:45.500
Was there a reason?

865
01:10:46.167 --> 01:10:48.167
The exact reason they hired me was

866
01:10:49.833 --> 01:10:53.083
Besides your extraordinary talent with numbers? There is.

867
01:10:54.500 --> 01:10:56.833
Have you been hiding that all this time?

868
01:10:57.667 --> 01:10:59.500
It's because I care about you.

869
01:11:00.250 --> 01:11:01.750
You have a mission to fulfill.

870
01:11:02.750 --> 01:11:05.167
We must not let anything get in the way.

871
01:11:08.333 --> 01:11:09.917
A Part of My Life

872
01:11:12.000 --> 01:11:13.417
Memories of my childhood

873
01:11:14.333 --> 01:11:16.750
There are things
I should know but don't.

874
01:11:20.917 --> 01:11:22.333
It just disappeared.

875
01:11:24.000 --> 01:11:25.583
It's really scary

876
01:11:26.833 --> 01:11:28.250
There's no need to be afraid

877
01:11:29.167 --> 01:11:31.750
I'm here.
There's someone else here. too.

878
01:11:32.167 --> 01:11:35.333
When the time comes. everything will become clear.

879
01:11:37.833 --> 01:11:40.667
Tomorrow morning.  I absolutely have to
go somewhere.

880
01:11:41.083 --> 01:11:43.667
Tomorrow will be
a day completely different from any other.

881
01:11:47.417 --> 01:11:48.917
Where should I go?

882
01:11:51.583 --> 01:11:52.750
KCXE?

883
01:11:53.583 --> 01:11:54.833
What is that?

884
01:12:37.750 --> 01:12:39.417
Do me a favor

885
01:12:39.583 --> 01:12:41.417
First. take a look at this

886
01:12:46.333 --> 01:12:47.833
Do you understand what she's saying?

887
01:12:49.333 --> 01:12:52.750
I can hear it. but it's so disjointed
I can't make head or tail of it.

888
01:12:53.667 --> 01:12:56.500
That's the first time I've heard of it.

889
01:12:57.000 --> 01:12:58.083
I understand

890
01:12:58.583 --> 01:12:59.583
It's in English.

891
01:12:59.750 --> 01:13:03.750
Or rather. it's math.
It gets converted into words in my head.

892
01:13:05.000 --> 01:13:07.667
When you look at this. it sounds like this

893
01:13:12.500 --> 01:13:14.667
Danny. I have a favor to ask.

894
01:13:23.750 --> 01:13:25.083
You have to doubt me

895
01:14:39.817 --> 01:14:40.817
I've got him!

896
01:15:32.833 --> 01:15:33.917
They're there

897
01:15:34.417 --> 01:15:35.333
They're here!

898
01:15:41.667 --> 01:15:43.417
- The bag!
- Go ahead

899
01:15:57.083 --> 01:15:59.333
- Hurry up
- That's all there is

900
01:16:00.500 --> 01:16:01.500
But you're coming. right?

901
01:16:03.500 --> 01:16:04.417
Break down the door!

902
01:16:07.500 --> 01:16:08.500
Take that with you.

903
01:16:10.500 --> 01:16:13.750
Please.
don't touch the contents.

904
01:16:30.083 --> 01:16:31.083
Get down!

905
01:16:34.500 --> 01:16:35.500
They're finished.

906
01:16:51.817 --> 01:16:52.817
I don't have a girlfriend.

907
01:16:58.250 --> 01:16:59.417
Where's the command?

908
01:17:40.500 --> 01:17:42.417
I took a wrong turn. Daniel.

909
01:17:43.083 --> 01:17:46.250
Let's talk later about
how much damage this has caused me.

910
01:17:47.250 --> 01:17:48.500
But  I finally got it

911
01:17:49.250 --> 01:17:50.833
The archive is safe.

912
01:17:51.000 --> 01:17:55.333
Now then.  tell me the names of
all your allies within Wardex.

913
01:17:55.583 --> 01:17:58.000
It's also unclear what Hugo is up to.

914
01:17:59.000 --> 01:18:00.083
But before that.

915
01:18:00.500 --> 01:18:02.167
Take that gear off

916
01:18:05.500 --> 01:18:08.000
Tell me
what you did with the command.

917
01:18:31.750 --> 01:18:33.667
Is it okay to drive that fast?

918
01:18:33.833 --> 01:18:36.250
You are Detective Thomas Farley

919
01:18:36.417 --> 01:18:39.417
That's registration number 389 339 8887. right?

920
01:18:40.333 --> 01:18:41.417
What's today's code?

921
01:18:42.917 --> 01:18:44.250
Kentucky-Philly

922
01:18:59.167 --> 01:19:00.250
Is that Agent Grady?

923
01:19:00.750 --> 01:19:02.500
Kentucky-Philly
Mr. Scanlon is waiting

924
01:19:02.667 --> 01:19:03.667
Follow me

925
01:19:50.333 --> 01:19:51.417
It's you.

926
01:19:58.917 --> 01:20:00.500
Margaret Fairchild

927
01:20:20.167 --> 01:20:21.250
Jocelyn

928
01:20:38.333 --> 01:20:39.333
Let her go!

929
01:20:39.667 --> 01:20:40.667
Don't interfere

930
01:20:58.583 --> 01:21:00.000
I know that.

931
01:21:12.083 --> 01:21:13.750
I know that. too.

932
01:21:14.417 --> 01:21:15.983
The two of them appear

933
01:21:16.500 --> 01:21:17.917
Don't let them leave the base

934
01:21:23.167 --> 01:21:24.167
Turn back!

935
01:21:24.333 --> 01:21:27.333
I waited too long to tell you.
It's too late now.

936
01:21:28.667 --> 01:21:31.000
But  even though I loved him
as if he were my own child

937
01:21:38.750 --> 01:21:41.833
Let's go to the lake on Friday.
Together with Grandpa and Grandma.

938
01:21:42.833 --> 01:21:45.333
Uncle Howard. Bobby. and Teresa

939
01:21:45.500 --> 01:21:46.667
Let's all...

940
01:21:58.917 --> 01:22:01.000
- How do you know them?
- I don't know them.

941
01:22:01.583 --> 01:22:03.083
But I was talking to him

942
01:22:09.167 --> 01:22:11.417
What's going on?
Hop in!

943
01:22:18.583 --> 01:22:19.667
What did you see?

944
01:22:22.000 --> 01:22:22.917
That's my wife.

945
01:22:28.083 --> 01:22:29.000
Oh my...

946
01:22:30.583 --> 01:22:31.750
Who is she?

947
01:22:33.500 --> 01:22:34.750
I have to stop her

948
01:22:47.000 --> 01:22:49.250
- Where are you going?
- To Kansas City.

949
01:22:50.250 --> 01:22:51.167
Why?

950
01:22:51.417 --> 01:22:52.417
I have to do that

951
01:22:52.583 --> 01:22:54.750
- You don't have to go that fast...
- No. you can't.

952
01:22:54.870 --> 01:22:58.453
- I'm having fun!
- Well... I guess I'm just in a good mood.

953
01:22:58.750 --> 01:23:00.833
But you know that. right?

954
01:23:01.000 --> 01:23:03.250
Lately. I've been driving really recklessly

955
01:23:03.500 --> 01:23:05.333
- How do you know that?
- I just know.

956
01:23:05.583 --> 01:23:09.583
Strange things have been happening lately.
and I've come to understand a lot of things.

957
01:23:09.833 --> 01:23:13.000
Even things I don't want to know—
and the opposite. too.

958
01:23:13.250 --> 01:23:15.250
So I decided to just let go

959
01:23:15.500 --> 01:23:18.083
That's amazing. Were you in prison?
That must have been tough...

960
01:23:20.333 --> 01:23:21.750
Hey. this feels weird.

961
01:23:22.667 --> 01:23:26.583
When I look at someone.
I suddenly find myself inside them.

962
01:23:27.750 --> 01:23:30.333
For a few seconds.
I become that person.

963
01:23:30.500 --> 01:23:31.917
What they went through

964
01:23:32.167 --> 01:23:34.083
It looks as if it's happening to me

965
01:23:35.000 --> 01:23:37.500
For example. let's say your shoulder hurts.

966
01:23:37.667 --> 01:23:38.667
You'll probably scream...

967
01:23:38.917 --> 01:23:39.833
Look ahead!

968
01:23:40.083 --> 01:23:43.250
I get it! You're thinking about Jane. aren't you?
She's supposed to be at the convent...

969
01:23:43.500 --> 01:23:45.000
- That's right.
- Jane

970
01:23:45.167 --> 01:23:46.083
Yesterday

971
01:23:46.333 --> 01:23:47.750
While driving with Jackson

972
01:23:48.000 --> 01:23:50.417
Even though I wasn't looking at you.
a flashback of you popped into my mind.

973
01:23:50.750 --> 01:23:53.667
It was really intense.
Even though I wasn't even looking at you.

974
01:23:53.817 --> 01:23:56.400
This is the first time this has ever happened to me.
I can't believe it.

975
01:23:56.750 --> 01:23:58.250
Since when?

976
01:23:58.500 --> 01:24:00.500
Since yesterday. ever since that bird...

977
01:24:01.083 --> 01:24:04.083
- A bird?
- A bird flew into the house.

978
01:24:04.250 --> 01:24:05.917
It was so beautiful that I couldn't take my eyes off it.

979
01:24:06.083 --> 01:24:07.000
Is that a cardinal (Japanese redstart)?

980
01:24:07.250 --> 01:24:09.833
Hey!
Don't scare me.

981
01:24:15.567 --> 01:24:16.900
When I was 20. at college……

982
01:24:17.167 --> 01:24:19.000
I hadn't studied much

983
01:24:19.250 --> 01:24:20.667
But he did have talent.

984
01:24:20.833 --> 01:24:23.750
Oh... but drugs at a party...
Ketamine? Are you serious?

985
01:24:24.000 --> 01:24:25.000
- Could you please stop?
- I'm sorry.

986
01:24:25.167 --> 01:24:26.833
When I was 20. at college

987
01:24:27.833 --> 01:24:29.667
At night. when I was in bed

988
01:24:29.833 --> 01:24:31.917
I had a dream that someone was watching me

989
01:24:32.417 --> 01:24:34.250
When I woke up. there was a bird...
- Is it a cardinal?

990
01:24:34.500 --> 01:24:36.417
……He was watching me from outside the window

991
01:24:36.667 --> 01:24:38.083
And then everything changed

992
01:24:38.333 --> 01:24:41.083
The Background and Patterns of Things  Distortions

993
01:24:41.250 --> 01:24:42.250
I could see everything now

994
01:24:42.417 --> 01:24:44.250
Matrices and Equations

995
01:24:44.500 --> 01:24:46.083
Just like the already solved "If P. then Q"

996
01:24:46.333 --> 01:24:48.583
Exactly!
I solved it without even thinking.

997
01:24:48.750 --> 01:24:51.167
So you were
reading binary code fluently. weren't you?

998
01:24:52.083 --> 01:24:54.167
- How do you know that?
- It's something you know yourself.

999
01:24:54.750 --> 01:24:55.667
You didn't like that.

1000
01:24:56.083 --> 01:24:57.333
I thought I was cursed

1001
01:24:57.500 --> 01:25:00.500
I became isolated and lost all my friends.

1002
01:25:00.750 --> 01:25:02.583
I couldn't connect with anyone anymore

1003
01:25:03.417 --> 01:25:04.417
Before I met Jane

1004
01:25:08.083 --> 01:25:09.583
"Don't be afraid of the unknown."

1005
01:25:09.750 --> 01:25:11.417
- What's that?
I heard that on TV.

1006
01:25:11.667 --> 01:25:12.833
No one understood

1007
01:25:13.000 --> 01:25:15.583
- I get it.
- What happened to us?

1008
01:25:20.583 --> 01:25:21.750
Who is it?

1009
01:25:23.917 --> 01:25:25.083
Void. stop it!

1010
01:25:37.333 --> 01:25:38.917
Get out!

1011
01:25:39.083 --> 01:25:40.583
No way. I'm slamming on the brakes.

1012
01:25:52.250 --> 01:25:53.500
I'm backing you up!  Go for it!

1013
01:26:18.583 --> 01:26:19.917
I can't reach the ladder!

1014
01:27:05.000 --> 01:27:06.000
Jump!

1015
01:27:19.667 --> 01:27:20.667
Jump!

1016
01:27:22.250 --> 01:27:23.500
Jump now!

1017
01:28:07.833 --> 01:28:09.000
I can't breathe

1018
01:28:11.583 --> 01:28:12.833
I can't... breathe

1019
01:28:14.667 --> 01:28:15.917
It's okay.

1020
01:28:16.500 --> 01:28:18.667
It's a panic attack.

1021
01:28:20.083 --> 01:28:21.833
Oh God. my hands...

1022
01:28:22.000 --> 01:28:24.083
- I know that.
- Just like Dad.

1023
01:28:24.250 --> 01:28:27.333
Dad's hands were shaking. too.
It's Parkinson's disease.

1024
01:28:27.917 --> 01:28:30.583
- No.  That's not it.
- No.

1025
01:28:30.750 --> 01:28:32.917
Just like Dad was shaking

1026
01:28:35.917 --> 01:28:39.417
Even though I’d been avoiding him.
I didn’t want to be near my father.

1027
01:28:40.167 --> 01:28:41.417
Stop it already!

1028
01:28:42.000 --> 01:28:43.333
Stop it already.

1029
01:28:44.833 --> 01:28:47.917
Just end it already.
I'm losing myself.

1030
01:28:48.083 --> 01:28:50.333
Stop it!  Be quiet!
Give me a hand.

1031
01:28:50.917 --> 01:28:54.000
- Look at me
- No. I don't want to see anything

1032
01:28:54.167 --> 01:28:55.750
Breathe through your nose

1033
01:28:57.667 --> 01:28:59.083
Yeah. keep it up.

1034
01:28:59.667 --> 01:29:01.167
I have no feeling in my hands

1035
01:29:03.250 --> 01:29:04.500
Reach out

1036
01:29:05.000 --> 01:29:06.250
Put it here

1037
01:29:06.667 --> 01:29:07.667
Can you feel it?

1038
01:29:08.917 --> 01:29:11.250
I'm here.
I'm with you.

1039
01:29:11.750 --> 01:29:12.917
It's over.

1040
01:29:14.417 --> 01:29:15.500
It's okay.

1041
01:29:33.333 --> 01:29:34.417
Thank you

1042
01:29:38.083 --> 01:29:40.333
Kerner called from Mount Leonard.

1043
01:29:40.500 --> 01:29:43.333
If I go with Santiago and the others.
we'll get there in two hours.

1044
01:29:48.667 --> 01:29:50.750
Everyone. step away from the set.

1045
01:29:51.083 --> 01:29:52.417
Right now!  Please!

1046
01:30:00.333 --> 01:30:01.417
